But also it just doesn't make sense to us.

17:30.114 --> 17:31.176
Because what do we value?

17:32.037 --> 17:32.698
How are we going to build?

17:32.718 --> 17:34.821
We're going to build a building.

17:34.841 --> 17:39.528
We're going to look at the finest things that are going to have the most solid foundation.

17:39.548 --> 17:42.813
We're not going to pick a weak concrete to build a foundation for a building, right?

17:43.173 --> 17:44.015
We value strength.

17:44.475 --> 17:46.759
Your experience is a parent with kids in sports.

17:46.799 --> 17:50.705
If your kid's not very good in athletics, no one's going to actually go talk to you.

17:51.065 --> 17:53.248
They don't care about you or your kid if you're not good.

17:54.070 --> 17:58.656
But if your kid's all of a sudden a star in the sport, other parents and other coaches, they'll come and talk to you, right?

17:59.317 --> 17:59.698
Why?

18:00.162 --> 18:02.526
Because I don't care about that kid, if he's not playing, he's on the bench.

18:02.546 --> 18:05.811
But I care about him, all of a sudden, because I want to feel good about myself.

18:05.851 --> 18:10.779
So I want to put myself next to other people that have position, of authority, of influence.

18:10.799 --> 18:12.342
We do this all over the place.

18:14.205 --> 18:16.449
It's part of who we are in the workplace.

18:17.210 --> 18:18.111
It's profound weakness.

18:18.973 --> 18:27.186
He was a passive man who lacked courage and gave his wife away, who had profound sexual immorality in his life.

18:27.682 --> 18:32.787
He was weak, yeah, God chose him and said, listen, through you, through your family, I'm gonna make a nation.

18:33.568 --> 18:38.933
Think about Moses who kills a man and runs off into the desert.

18:39.653 --> 18:41.115
When does God come drawn near to him?

18:41.155 --> 18:43.217
It's actually in his weakest moment when he's by himself.

18:43.898 --> 18:44.638
God draws near to him.

18:44.658 --> 18:49.823
And remember when he goes back to like be God's voice, he's like, hey, I can't, my voice isn't strong enough.

18:50.704 --> 18:56.850
He's a passive man, he's a weak man, yet God still says, okay, I'll give you somebody to speak through and I'll figure this out for you.

18:57.698 --> 18:58.199
There's one more.

18:58.219 --> 18:59.060
I mean, think about David.

18:59.400 --> 19:00.182
Great King David.

19:01.584 --> 19:02.845
God made one of his covenants with.

19:03.526 --> 19:08.894
You know, if you remember the story when he was like going to be picked, it's like, no, not the strong one, not that one, not that one, not that one.

19:09.495 --> 19:10.536
I think you've got another son.

19:10.576 --> 19:13.440
Think about if you heard your dad, I would never say this to you guys.

19:13.601 --> 19:15.143
Think about if you heard your dad saying this about you.

19:15.163 --> 19:15.984
Yeah, he's got that.

19:16.785 --> 19:18.127
I got another son, but he's small.

19:18.147 --> 19:18.648
He's scrawny.

19:18.668 --> 19:20.931
He's pretty lame watching the sheep.

19:20.951 --> 19:21.732
I don't think you want him.

19:21.812 --> 19:23.635
And Sam was like, no, I want him.

19:24.757 --> 19:25.778
This is what God does.

19:26.818 --> 19:28.221
This is what He's always done.

19:28.241 --> 19:30.064
It should not surprise us.

19:31.326 --> 19:34.172
God is not impressed with your strength because your strength is nothing.

19:35.494 --> 19:39.462
He's impressed when you can be honest about the truth of your existence is that you are weak.

19:40.343 --> 19:41.806
You are a needy person.

19:43.489 --> 19:45.693
And it's in weakness that Jesus Himself came.

19:45.713 --> 19:48.558
He who was rich became poor.

19:48.599 --> 19:50.482
Why that you might become rich.

19:50.978 --> 19:53.843
He who was strong, put on the weakness of flesh.

19:53.903 --> 19:54.505
He had hunger.

19:54.545 --> 19:55.246
He had sorrow.

19:55.286 --> 19:55.887
He had pain.

19:55.927 --> 19:58.452
He put himself on the cross.

19:59.093 --> 19:59.313
Why?

19:59.353 --> 20:02.860
To show us that the pathway to blessing is not despite our weakness, but through it.

20:04.924 --> 20:14.802
Or the pathway to being, to fulfilling the promises that God's made to his people, to this world is not your mind's strength and our ability to be impressive and to speak well.

20:15.394 --> 20:17.296
You guys know I'm horrible at speaking.

20:17.316 --> 20:21.841
I always say things backwards and you guys create memes about it and it's really encouraging to me.

20:22.702 --> 20:24.023
Like this is what God does though.

20:24.163 --> 20:29.028
He uses our weakness and in that he builds.

20:30.690 --> 20:33.573
The pathway to blessing is not to spite our weakness but through it.

20:33.853 --> 20:37.697
God does not abandon us in our weakness but he comes and draws near precisely in our weakness.

20:41.101 --> 20:42.162
We're never not weak.

20:43.522 --> 20:46.707
And where weakness is actually not a liability, it's our greatest asset.

20:46.988 --> 20:51.274
And this is a great mystery of the church that Paul sums up perfectly in 2 Corinthians 12.

20:51.314 --> 20:53.598
And my power has been perfect in weakness.

20:55.241 --> 20:55.902
This is what he does.

20:57.284 --> 21:00.529
So yes, we are filled with a weak people.

21:01.250 --> 21:05.818
People who struggle to be passive, people who struggle with our sin, we are hypocrites in that way.

21:08.422 --> 21:11.026
But whenever God actually builds something good through us,

21:12.226 --> 21:18.737
God won't see our, people won't see our strength, but they'll see the might of God that can build through weak people.

21:19.779 --> 21:33.643
And to belong to the church is to recognize our need, not hiding it by embracing it, embracing our weakness, being open about our weaknesses, because it is the pathway to blessing, which is the second thing we see here.

21:33.703 --> 21:35.186
First, we see churches weak,

21:37.698 --> 21:42.544
Second, we see that the church is blessed, and the way to be blessed is to embrace our weakness.

21:43.826 --> 21:48.452
You see this blessing language all throughout this future that he gives to Joseph.

21:49.113 --> 22:07.698
But there's something about this language that, and about all of this, it's, there's always broader than just the one person is speaking to the one person, but these people are representative tribes, and those tribes find the fulfillment actually in the church, and so there's a handful, for biblical interpretation reasons, there's a handful of different ways you could take

22:07.778 --> 22:09.960
a lot of these different things, and you'd be right to do so.

22:10.501 --> 22:20.651
When I'm looking at this blessing to Joseph, I'm gonna take it more in the corporate sense, and how it applies to us, because I think all of these things ultimately apply to us directly.

22:21.071 --> 22:36.146
But you see this in verse 25 to 26, where it says, by the God of your Father, who will help you by the Almighty, who will bless you with blessings of heaven above, blessings of the deep, that crouches beneath, blessings of the breasts and of the womb,

22:36.578 --> 22:40.523
The blessings of your father are mighty beyond the blessing of my parents.

22:42.426 --> 22:45.450
Up to the bounties of the everlasting hills.

22:46.652 --> 22:50.918
May they be on the head of Joseph and on the brow of him who was set apart from his brothers.

22:50.938 --> 22:58.108
And he gives us this language of blessing is excessive and it kind of piles up over and over.

22:59.930 --> 23:05.458
Blessings with heaven above from the deep that crouches beneath and the blessings of the breast and of the woman.

23:06.434 --> 23:12.981
And if Jacob, as he's looking at his sons, he must see just their flaws, their burdens.

23:14.703 --> 23:16.886
And here we get this pronouncement of abundance.

23:18.748 --> 23:22.452
This over the top of blessings.

23:23.633 --> 23:35.026
If you think about Joseph specifically for a second, he knows his weakness, his life has been martyred pain as he was a slave, he was forgotten false accusations.

23:35.714 --> 23:37.296
But there's this pronouncement of blessing.

23:37.316 --> 23:39.058
What is this blessing ultimately about?

23:39.078 --> 23:42.663
I think ultimately this is about God's presence, right?

23:42.703 --> 23:45.207
The blessing of heaven above, what is heaven?

23:45.727 --> 23:48.571
Heaven is a place where God dwells, it's where His presence is.

23:50.033 --> 23:54.659
To be blessed with, the heaven above is to be blessed with the very presence of God here with you.

23:55.400 --> 23:57.703
Heaven on earth, heaven in our souls.

23:57.903 --> 23:59.926
This Christ spirit lives and dwells within us.

24:01.448 --> 24:02.930
This is this blessing of,

24:03.298 --> 24:05.101
of presence and everything flows from that.

24:05.201 --> 24:06.923
Blessings of the deep that crouches beneath.

24:07.504 --> 24:11.430
Blessings of the breast of the woman, the breast and of the womb.

24:12.452 --> 24:15.857
Wow.

24:16.378 --> 24:18.581
So I told you, I told you I'm weak and I say the wrong things.

24:18.641 --> 24:21.045
I don't ever get that out of the recording.

24:23.048 --> 24:23.829
But what is that about?

24:24.350 --> 24:25.912
It's about fruitfulness, right?

24:26.353 --> 24:27.314
It's about the blessing

24:27.490 --> 24:28.311
But you're going to be fruitful.

24:28.331 --> 24:30.755
You're going to multiply until the children cover the earth.

24:30.775 --> 24:31.596
That's what this is about.

24:31.616 --> 24:32.297
There's this joy.

24:32.337 --> 24:33.358
There's this presence of God.

24:33.378 --> 24:34.140
There's fruitfulness.

24:34.821 --> 24:35.622
It's heaven on earth.

24:35.702 --> 24:37.144
It's all is right in this world.

24:37.244 --> 24:40.889
It's the end of revelations, renewal of all things.

24:41.670 --> 24:42.832
This is what this blessing is.

24:43.613 --> 24:49.041
It's God's presence with his people that despite our troubles, despite our weakness, God is with us.

24:50.683 --> 24:54.088
And it's our weakness that draws him to us and us to him.

24:54.128 --> 24:55.410
And as we're drawn to him,

24:55.778 --> 24:58.241
refill with His presence, the blessing of His presence.

25:00.905 --> 25:06.493
You know, oftentimes when you think of blessing, we tend to think purely in material senses.

25:07.334 --> 25:11.780
This is so much bigger than prosperity, than so much easier than the ease of life.

25:13.022 --> 25:18.249
It's God Himself to creators, the sustainer of all things with you and with me.

25:21.233 --> 25:22.194
It's God with us.

25:23.618 --> 25:28.923
And He always draws near to His people when they learn to embrace their weakness.

25:31.926 --> 25:33.227
This is when He comes to our life.

25:33.287 --> 25:40.394
This is when our blessings or His presence is felt most succinctly, is in our weakness.

25:40.955 --> 25:41.756
It's in the darkness.

25:43.037 --> 25:43.998
Why does that often happen?

25:44.018 --> 25:46.840
It's to remind us that your strength is not what holds you.

25:46.860 --> 25:48.822
It's not your ability to hold on and endure.

25:48.882 --> 25:50.184
It's His in you.

25:50.924 --> 25:52.626
You know, there's that silly

25:53.442 --> 25:56.907
picture that was probably hanging on her walls, maybe it's still hanging on your wall.

25:56.967 --> 25:58.609
I'm sorry, I'm going to make fun of it a little bit.

25:58.909 --> 26:05.918
But you know the footprints of the sand thing, where it's like the guy looks back and you know, they only see one set of footprints because God was carrying them all along.

26:06.499 --> 26:13.648
And it's kind of this goofy image, most of you probably seen it, but there's actually a lot of truth actually in that image, isn't there?

26:14.590 --> 26:16.232
So you don't have to feel bad if it's on your wall.

26:16.512 --> 26:17.914
There's a lot of truth.

26:17.974 --> 26:21.138
It's cheesy, but there's truth that our strength happens

26:21.506 --> 26:22.828
It's not our own strength.

26:22.868 --> 26:26.334
And anytime we have strength, it's because of his working in us and through us.

26:28.096 --> 26:32.503
And those times of hardship in our lives only grow our dependence on his strength.

26:34.006 --> 26:39.134
There's another thing that people use to make fun of Christians, say, you know, Christianity is just a crutch for you.

26:40.095 --> 26:40.997
Absolutely it is.

26:41.017 --> 26:42.219
100%.

26:42.539 --> 26:43.861
And it's a pretty darn good crutch.

26:43.881 --> 26:44.703
It's more than a crutch.

26:44.743 --> 26:45.664
It's the wheelchair.

26:45.684 --> 26:49.330
It's the, I don't know, I'm fully dependent on it for everything.

26:49.570 --> 26:50.611
It 100% is a crutch.

26:50.631 --> 26:51.552
It's actually meant to be.

26:51.893 --> 26:53.014
You always will need it.

26:54.115 --> 26:57.859
The whole point of a crutch is that you're too weak to like carry yourself and that's right.

26:57.979 --> 26:59.461
You are too weak to live this life.

27:00.502 --> 27:01.763
You're not going to be a good enough father.

27:01.783 --> 27:02.985
You're not going to be a good enough husband.

27:03.005 --> 27:06.128
You're not going to be a good enough wife, mother, daughter, son.

27:06.188 --> 27:07.950
You cannot hold these things together.

27:08.751 --> 27:09.712
You will make mistakes.

27:11.734 --> 27:14.016
Today, this afternoon, right now, you're going to make them.

27:15.338 --> 27:19.122
You need something to hold you together and Christ says, come to me and I will bless you.

27:20.578 --> 27:25.305
Because you are weak, because you can't do this yourself, come to me, I'll be your strength.

27:26.246 --> 27:26.747
Lean on me.

27:28.209 --> 27:31.313
I think you get a sense that Jacob is understanding what's happening.

27:32.374 --> 27:39.144
In verse 18, it's this strange verse in the midst of all these blessings, it's like him speaking his own personal prayer to God.

27:40.005 --> 27:42.669
Verse 18, I will wait for your salvation, O Lord.

27:42.689 --> 27:44.611
It's a strange interruption.

27:45.232 --> 27:47.375
I wait, I wait for you to what?

27:47.395 --> 27:49.298
To save your people.

27:49.506 --> 27:55.294
Your people, my children, the nations that will flow, the tribes that will flow from my trust you, I'm gonna wait for you to actually do this work.

27:56.335 --> 27:56.996
What is this about?

27:57.036 --> 27:59.379
I think he knows that the end of his life is he's about to die.

27:59.399 --> 28:01.042
He knows he can't control this anymore.

28:02.323 --> 28:06.349
He's not gonna have any more influence on what his sons do and how they handle life.

28:09.072 --> 28:09.913
He can't control it.

28:09.934 --> 28:16.242
And if there's few things in life that expose your lack of control in this world, then parenting.

28:17.282 --> 28:20.625
Right, parents, you know this, it exposes that you can't control your children.

28:23.949 --> 28:28.413
You can't control the outcomes, you can't control what they do in life, you can't control a whole lot.

28:29.014 --> 28:32.937
You know, years ago, I used to be able to control who they marry, but I think that's frowned upon now.

28:33.198 --> 28:36.341
No more buying a son of goats or something like that for weddings.

28:38.903 --> 28:40.105
But this is what this is about.

28:41.106 --> 28:45.650
This is what this waiting is, exposing this lack of control and to wait

28:46.466 --> 28:50.472
I think is the ultimate acknowledgement of both weakness and blessing.

28:51.774 --> 28:53.698
To wait is to say, I can't do this myself.

28:53.758 --> 28:54.659
I have to wait here.

28:55.380 --> 28:57.303
I can't force myself through this line.

28:58.024 --> 29:03.293
I got to just stay here and I got to be patient and I got to wait because I'm weak.

29:05.076 --> 29:14.130
And it's waiting on the Lord is trusting in the Lord to move, trusting that the blessing of His presence will come to you because He promised it and He never forsakes His promises.

29:14.338 --> 29:16.441
What is the promises most often repeated in Scripture?

29:16.501 --> 29:18.184
Do not fear, right?

29:18.524 --> 29:19.406
For I am with you.

29:19.446 --> 29:21.489
His presence is what he promises as people.

29:23.492 --> 29:24.514
I can wait for it then.

29:25.535 --> 29:28.860
And as we wait for it, salvation comes, blessing comes.

29:28.880 --> 29:29.842
His presence comes.

29:30.743 --> 29:43.122
And not only does the blessing come to you and me, his presence come to me, but we are actually, as we're blessed, then blessing flows out of this place to the end of the world.

29:44.834 --> 29:46.376
We've become a blessing in this moment.

29:47.077 --> 29:52.645
You know, the church as flat as she is, this is the place that the blessings flow to the end of the world.

29:53.286 --> 30:00.235
It's not in the political arena, it's not in the hospitals, it's not in the education systems, it's not any other institution.

30:01.917 --> 30:05.763
Those are great, and I'm for all of them, and we should be involved in all these things.

30:06.784 --> 30:11.190
But the chief institution that rules all of their institutions is the institution of the church.

30:12.492 --> 30:14.034
This is where blessings flow

30:14.146 --> 30:14.887
into the world.

30:16.569 --> 30:18.090
Because what we offer is not ourselves.

30:19.292 --> 30:22.596
But the presence of God has got us present with us in a unique way as we gather.

30:22.676 --> 30:27.301
As his people, as a church, we bring that presence with us when we go out into this world.

30:28.022 --> 30:29.163
This is how it's always been.

30:29.183 --> 30:32.187
This is the truth to Adam and Eve in the garden.

30:32.387 --> 30:38.854
They were blessed to decide to expand his presence in the world, to Abraham, to the disciples, to us.

30:40.216 --> 30:42.258
It's all about expansion of God's presence.

30:42.466 --> 30:44.789
in this world which happens through His people.

30:46.912 --> 30:49.675
Because we are the place that God's presence dwells in the world.

30:49.716 --> 30:51.177
This is what sets you and I apart.

30:51.818 --> 30:54.622
It's not our perfection, but it's the presence of Christ among us.

30:54.662 --> 30:55.743
That is His blessing on us.

30:57.466 --> 31:05.036
This is why even if the church has lost all cultural impact which throughout its life and ebbs and flows, it has all finances.

31:06.017 --> 31:09.842
Even if she has nothing, gathering and catacombs, surviving,

31:11.106 --> 31:18.234
hiding in the back rooms and churches in China, she still and always will be the strongest force on the earth.

31:19.855 --> 31:21.557
What does Jesus say about the church?

31:21.577 --> 31:23.019
I don't think we think about this enough.

31:23.039 --> 31:25.882
The gates of hell shall not prevail against it.

31:26.883 --> 31:28.585
That is not a throwaway line.

31:29.145 --> 31:29.906
That is the line.

31:30.927 --> 31:37.394
And again, he's not speaking about one specific church like St. Andrew's gonna come and go, but the church will never fail.

31:38.434 --> 31:42.400
Hell itself, the thing that anyone that fears anything, you're gonna fear hell, right?

31:43.221 --> 31:44.944
Has nothing and will not prevail.

31:45.885 --> 31:46.306
The church.

31:48.469 --> 31:49.491
It's a powerful statement.

31:49.631 --> 31:55.119
The strongest thing on this earth right now is God's presence and His presence is here through the church.

31:57.002 --> 32:02.190
This is how God dwells on the earth right now and this is how He's expanding His kingdom and His dwelling place on this earth.

32:02.771 --> 32:04.493
You know, it's super in vogue.

32:04.914 --> 32:05.675
I hear it all the time.

32:05.755 --> 32:07.538
I see it on the inner webs

32:07.650 --> 32:09.713
People will say, well, you know, the church is dumb.

32:09.733 --> 32:10.413
You don't really need it.

32:10.834 --> 32:13.537
I went to it for a bit, but it's messy.

32:13.577 --> 32:14.859
I didn't really like it.

32:14.899 --> 32:16.060
The people are weird.

32:16.100 --> 32:16.881
I don't have time.

32:16.941 --> 32:17.582
I'm too busy.

32:17.622 --> 32:18.603
I'm doing this and that.

32:19.304 --> 32:20.806
I'll find God on my own.

32:21.907 --> 32:24.771
When I have brunch with my friends, God's with me there.

32:24.831 --> 32:28.616
Or if I go to the trees, you know, it's God's there.

32:29.737 --> 32:31.960
And, you know, I do agree that it's messy.

32:32.420 --> 32:32.981
It's weird.

32:33.281 --> 32:35.264
Even those communities were weird, guys.

32:35.664 --> 32:37.106
It's okay.

32:38.946 --> 32:44.414
But you can't find God in the trees like you can find him here with his people.

32:45.335 --> 32:48.319
Because he dwells with his gathered people in a unique way.

32:48.760 --> 32:49.321
He always has.

32:49.361 --> 32:59.355
And the church cannot be blessed apart from God with us, and the world cannot be blessed apart from us in the world.

33:00.837 --> 33:05.264
Our witness to the world is not our perfection, but it's our Savior's perfection.

33:05.584 --> 33:06.866
It is in our strength that we

33:07.298 --> 33:09.160
show the world, but it's the strength of Christ.

33:09.200 --> 33:12.744
To be able to admit that, yeah, we are weak, yeah, we have nothing, but Christ does everything.

33:12.824 --> 33:14.806
Come, be a part of this kingdom.

33:15.627 --> 33:17.789
And when does Christ show His strength the most?

33:19.832 --> 33:20.472
It's on the cross.

33:21.213 --> 33:27.500
And the story of Jesus, one of the most amazing things is it's when He's hanging on the cross and one of the centurion soldiers finally recognizes who He is.

33:28.581 --> 33:29.743
Surely He is the Son of Man.

33:30.904 --> 33:32.506
Surely He is the guy He thought He was.

33:33.146 --> 33:36.530
When He's hanging on a cross, dying, that's when He recognized Him.

33:37.762 --> 33:38.683
It's not an accident.

33:40.845 --> 33:44.610
Jesus defeated death by putting himself underneath it.

33:46.872 --> 33:57.644
As he breaks free from those chains of death and rises to new life, and he's leading you and I along the same path, death to resurrection, weakness to blessing, death to life.

33:57.884 --> 33:58.585
This is our life.

33:59.286 --> 34:02.810
And what this means for you and me is a couple of things.

34:02.870 --> 34:04.992
First is that you don't need to hide your weakness.

34:06.434 --> 34:06.834
You don't.

34:07.202 --> 34:08.804
Your weakness is your strength.

34:09.945 --> 34:16.073
Your weakness is the thing that qualifies you to receive the gospel.

34:16.133 --> 34:17.835
Don't hide your weakness.

34:18.956 --> 34:19.777
Don't be embarrassed.

34:21.379 --> 34:29.209
It's only embracing our weakness that Christ's power is made perfect in us, because it's made perfect in our weakness, not running from it.

34:29.850 --> 34:36.498
The second thing is we need to double in down on our commitment to the things that are lasting, to being a part of this, people of God, it is hard.

34:36.994 --> 34:37.735
You will get wounded.

34:38.516 --> 34:39.177
It is messy.

34:39.858 --> 34:42.542
But not only will you get wounded, you're going to actually do some of the wounding.

34:44.144 --> 34:44.865
It's full disclosure.

34:44.925 --> 34:46.107
It'll happen both directions.

34:46.147 --> 34:47.809
This is a two-way street.

34:50.713 --> 34:53.036
And to be part of this community, it creates humility to see that.

34:53.577 --> 34:54.418
This goes both ways.

34:55.059 --> 34:55.920
It doesn't excuse it.

34:56.401 --> 34:59.145
We're not trying to excuse the wounding either direction.

34:59.185 --> 35:00.226
We confess those things.

35:00.246 --> 35:00.767
We repent.

35:00.807 --> 35:02.349
We work those things out.

35:03.130 --> 35:03.831
But it's going to happen.

35:05.333 --> 35:05.874
Expect it.

35:06.210 --> 35:08.994
Expectation is nine-tenths of the law or something.

35:11.277 --> 35:15.744
Clearly, I said that backwards on purpose, guys, just, you know, I do know sometimes when I do that.

35:17.507 --> 35:23.015
But this is for us to embrace, to be a part of, to double down the commitment to the things that are lasting, the thing that is a church.

35:23.115 --> 35:24.257
This is who God called us to be.

35:25.579 --> 35:31.708
What sets us apart is not our strength, but the presence of God who is the strength in us and among us.

35:32.629 --> 35:36.114
And we learn and grow to be a people who boast in our weakness

35:37.154 --> 35:40.818
May we trust in the ever strong power of God to be a blessing in the world.

35:42.360 --> 35:42.820
Pray with me.

35:47.966 --> 35:49.567
Holy God, we give you thanks for your word.

35:49.607 --> 36:04.023
I pray that you would help us to acknowledge and see our weakness, our inability to pull ourselves up by our own bootstraps, but our need of you.

36:04.964 --> 36:07.026
I pray that you grow our dependence on you

36:07.458 --> 36:08.160
and all things.

36:10.006 --> 36:16.307
And I pray that you would help us to be a light, to be a blessing in this place that you've called us.

36:18.052 --> 36:18.995
We pray this in your holy name.

36:19.497 --> 36:19.858
Amen.

